.\audits\2026-07-10-round9\codex-run.log:697:.\audits\2026-07-10-round9\AUDIT_PROMPT.md:16:Independently look for ANY remaining publication-blocker at the manuscript/repository level. In particular, note that repo-wide sweeps were just done for: propagation overclaims, "E7 as current arbiter", "equal information budget", and unbannered retired multipliers (2.19x/2.22x/2.26x) — verify these are genuinely clean (every non-historical file bearing those magnitudes should carry a retirement banner; audit reports under audits/2026-07-10/ and dated external-review/manuscript-v1.6-round/ files are legitimately historical). Also check: claim exceeds evidence; internal contradiction; stale local metadata; dead reference; EN/ES desync; simulation text vs shipped script; statistic provenance (median 0.025 pre-registered vs post-hoc 0.026). Ignore author-gated deposit-time actions (live Zenodo metadata edit, mixed CC-BY/MIT in .zenodo.json, full v1.13 reviewer-packet rewrite, the v1.13 deposit) — confirm each is correctly flagged/deferred.
