.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:271:The manuscript introduction and conclusion (`drafts/paper.md:120-124,1277-1282`) and the public companion (`docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:5-12,783-794`) present pooled ~0.026 as the pre-registered gate result. The controlling result is: **pre-registered pooled median Δ = 0.025, below the 0.05 research-program rebuild threshold; NO-GO**. The **post-hoc** ratio-of-sums is **Δ = 0.026 [0.023, 0.029]** and must be a separate sentence. Replace bare “materiality gate/bar” language on README, companion, contract, and paper summaries with the rebuild-only, uncalibrated interpretation.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:313:### 1. Major — The introduction, conclusion, and public companion attribute the post-hoc 0.026 estimate to the pre-registered gate
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:316:- **Contradicting side:** the governing Section 6 account says, “the **pre-registered decision statistic** is the **pooled median Δ = 0.025**” (`drafts/paper.md:542`) and then separately says “a **post-hoc** ratio-of-sums estimate is **Δ = 0.026**” (`drafts/paper.md:543`–`drafts/paper.md:544`). The controlling contract likewise distinguishes “pre-registered pooled **median Δ ≈ 0.025**” (`research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md:63`) from “the pooled ratio-of-sums ... **Δ = 0.026**” (`research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md:64`) and requires the latter to be “reported separately from the median” (`research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md:66`).
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:317:- **What is wrong:** the introduction says that “a pre-registered, symmetric, selection-only stress test shrinks” the advantage “to a pooled ~0.026” (`drafts/paper.md:120`–`drafts/paper.md:122`). The conclusion is more explicit: “a pre-registered, symmetric, selection-only gate finds” (`drafts/paper.md:1277`–`drafts/paper.md:1278`) “a pooled ~0.026” (`drafts/paper.md:1279`). Both companion summaries repeat the same attribution: the “pre-registered symmetry gate” showed “a pooled ~0.026” (`docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:7`–`docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:8`), and the later “pre-registered ... stress test” returned a “pooled ~0.026” (`docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:785`–`docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:790`). The number is not numerically false; its inferential label is false. It is the post-hoc ratio-of-sums, not the pre-registered decision statistic.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:318:- **Why it matters:** this recreates the exact median-versus-ratio conflation the controlling contract was written to prohibit, including in the conclusion and the Zenodo-promoted accessible companion. A reader can reasonably conclude that 0.026 was the frozen gate statistic and miss that its interval is post-hoc Monte Carlo uncertainty conditional on the simulated DGP.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:319:- **Concrete fix:** in every short summary of the gate, report “pre-registered pooled median Δ = 0.025, below the 0.05 research-program rebuild gate.” If 0.026 is retained outside Section 6, add a separate sentence: “A post-hoc ratio-of-sums was Δ = 0.026 with a 95% world-cluster Monte-Carlo interval [0.023, 0.029].” Apply this to the introduction, conclusion, and both companion summaries.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:341:- **What is wrong:** README and both companion summaries stop at “0.05 materiality gate,” and even the controlling contract calls it a “materiality bar” without naming the research-rebuild purpose at that point. These statements are not numerically inconsistent, but their semantics are inconsistent across the controlling and public surfaces.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:362:### 1. Major — Gate summaries use the post-hoc 0.026 estimate as though it were the pre-registered decision statistic, and continue to call 0.05 a materiality threshold
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:365:- **What is wrong:** The paper's governing paragraph gets the distinction right: “the pre-registered decision statistic is the pooled median Δ = 0.025” and “a post-hoc ratio-of-sums estimate is Δ = 0.026” (`drafts/paper.md:542-545`). The contribution summary instead says the pre-registered stress test produced “a pooled ~0.026 ... below its 0.05 materiality gate” (`drafts/paper.md:120-123`); Finding 7 again attributes ~0.026 to “the later pre-registered symmetric test” (`drafts/paper.md:942-946`); and the conclusion repeats ~0.026 as the figure below the gate (`drafts/paper.md:1277-1280`). The public companion makes the same substitution twice (`docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:5-12`, `docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:783-794`). The frozen pre-registration defines per-world Δ and gates the **pooled median** at 0.05; the ratio-of-sums and its world-cluster interval were computed later and are explicitly post-hoc. Separately, `README.md:31`, `docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:8-9`, `docs/101_CORE_V0_MINIMAL_PUBLISHABLE_MODEL.md:789-790`, and the two paper summaries call 0.05 a “materiality gate,” although the settled interpretation is a research-program rebuild/no-rebuild threshold on an uncalibrated scale, not policy materiality. Even the contract's shorthand “materiality bar” at `research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md:63-68` leaves this distinction less explicit than the governing paper paragraph.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:367:- **Concrete fix:** Standardize every gate summary to: “pre-registered pooled median Δ = 0.025, below the pre-set 0.05 research-program rebuild threshold; NO-GO.” Where useful, add a separate sentence: “A post-hoc ratio-of-sums estimate was Δ = 0.026 with a world-cluster Monte-Carlo interval [0.023, 0.029].” Never compare 0.026 directly to the gate, and replace bare “materiality gate/bar” with “research-program rebuild threshold (not a calibrated policy-materiality threshold)” in the contract and all public summaries.
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:452:**What is wrong:** The correction banner says the result is “a pooled ~0.026 ... below its 0.05 materiality gate” (`docs/101...:8-9`), and the computational section repeats “a pooled ~0.026 ... below its 0.05 materiality gate” (`docs/101...:789-790`). The controlling contract keeps two estimators distinct: the **pre-registered pooled median is ~0.025 and is the statistic judged against the 0.05 gate**, while **0.026 [0.023, 0.029] is a post-hoc world-cluster ratio-of-sums plus Monte Carlo interval** (`research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md:62-66`).
.\audits\2026-07-10-round4\codex-run.log:456:**Concrete fix:** In both locations, state separately: “pre-registered pooled median Δ = 0.025, below the pre-registered 0.05 research-rebuild gate; post-hoc pooled ratio-of-sums Δ = 0.026, world-cluster Monte Carlo interval [0.023, 0.029].” Also say the 0.05 threshold is a research-rebuild threshold, not a policy-materiality threshold.
