  110: ## Standard review routine
  111: 
  112: For each attack:
  113: 
  114: 1. read the attack file;
  115: 2. read the paired defense file under `defenses/`;
  116: 3. verify the project locations cited in both files;
  117: 4. test the stress scenario against the current architecture;
  118: 5. decide whether the accepted resolution is enough, whether core propagation is needed, or whether residual risk remains unresolved;
  119: 6. update the roadmap, indexes, and affected core documents;
  120: 7. update formal inventory, schema, or diagrams where the resolution adds objects, fields, tests, or states;
